cv_splits = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=random_state)
ct = ColumnTransformer(
    [("standardization", StandardScaler(), ['Air temperature [K]', 'Process temperature [K]', 'Rotational speed [rpm]', 'Torque [Nm]', 'Tool wear [min]']),], remainder='passthrough')

def train_model(X_train, y_train, pipe, params, scores=None):
    if scores is None:
        scores = ['f1']
    search = GridSearchCV(pipe,
                          params,
                          cv=cv_splits,
                          scoring=scores,
                          refit=scores[0],
                          n_jobs=-1,
                          verbose=1)
    search.fit(X_train, y_train.values.ravel())
    return search

def print_test_scores(model, multiclass=False):
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    y_pred_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)
    test_acc = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)

    print("\nTest Scores:")
    # if multiclass:
    #     test_precision, test_recall, test_f1, _ = precision_recall_fscore_support(y_test, y_pred, average='macro')
    #     auc_score = round(roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred_proba, average='macro', multi_class='ovr'), 4)

    #     print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, digits=3))
    # else:
    #     test_precision, test_recall, test_f1, _ = precision_recall_fscore_support(y_test, y_pred, average='binary')
    #     auc_score = round(roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred_proba[:,1]), 4)

    #     print(f"- Precision: {round(test_precision, 3)}")
    #     print(f"- Recall: {round(test_recall, 3)}")
    #     print(f"- F1-score: {round(test_f1, 3)}")
    #     print(f"- Accuracy: {round(test_acc, 3)}")
    #     print(f'- ROC AUC: {round(auc_score, 3)}')

    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, digits=3))

    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
    gs = gridspec.GridSpec(2, 2, hspace=0.3, figure=fig)
    ax1 = plt.subplot(gs[:, 0])
    ax2 = plt.subplot(gs[0, 1])
    ax3 = plt.subplot(gs[1, 1])

    plot_confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred, ax=ax1)
    plot_roc_curve(model, X_test, y_test, ax=ax2, multiclass=multiclass)
    plot_prec_recall_curve(model, X_test, y_test, ax=ax3, multiclass=multiclass)

    current_plot = plt.gcf()
    plt.show()

    return current_plot

def plot_confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred, ax):
    # print(confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred))

    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
    cm_norm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred, normalize='true')

    # off_diag_mask = np.eye(*cm.shape, dtype=bool)
    # vmin = np.min(cm)
    # vmax = np.max(cm)
    # sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, mask=~off_diag_mask, cmap='Greens', ax=ax, square=True,
    #             cbar=True, vmin=vmin, vmax=vmax, cbar_kws={"shrink": .5, "pad": -0.1})
    # sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, mask=off_diag_mask, cmap='Greys', ax=ax, square=True,
    #             cbar=True, vmin=vmin, vmax=vmax, cbar_kws={"shrink": .5, "ticks": []})

    # sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, cmap=sns.color_palette("Blues", as_cmap=True),
    #             ax=ax, square=True, cbar=True, cbar_kws={"shrink": .6})
    
    group_counts = [f"{value:0.0f}" for value in cm.flatten()]
    group_percentages = [f"{value:.2%}" for value in cm_norm.flatten()]
    group_percentages = [f"{value:.2%}" if value != 0 else '' for value in cm_norm.flatten()]

    labels = [f"{v1}\n{v2}" if v1 != '' else f"{v2}" for v1, v2 in zip(group_percentages, group_counts)]
    labels = np.asarray(labels).reshape(cm.shape[0], cm.shape[0])

    if cm.shape[0] > 2:
        annot_font_size = 12
    else:
        annot_font_size = 14

    sns.heatmap(cm_norm, 
                annot=labels, annot_kws={"fontsize": annot_font_size},
                cmap=sns.color_palette("Blues", as_cmap=True),
                square=True, 
                cbar=True, cbar_kws={"shrink": .6},
                vmin=0,
                vmax=1,
                fmt='',
                ax=ax)
    
    cbar = ax.collections[0].colorbar
    cbar.set_ticks(list(np.linspace(0, 1.0, num=6)), labels=['0%', '20%', '40%', '60%', '80%', '100%'])
    ax.set_xlabel('\nPredicted Values')
    ax.set_ylabel('Actual Values')

def plot_roc_curve(model, X_test, y_test, ax, multiclass=False):
    if multiclass:
        y_test_binarized = label_binarize(y_test, classes=[0, 1, 2, 3, 4])
        y_score = model.predict_proba(X_test)
        n_classes = y_test_binarized.shape[1]

        fpr = dict()
        tpr = dict()
        roc_auc = dict()
        for i in range(n_classes):
            fpr[i], tpr[i], _ = roc_curve(y_test_binarized[:, i], y_score[:, i])
            roc_auc[i] = auc(fpr[i], tpr[i])

        for i in range(n_classes):
            ax.plot(fpr[i], tpr[i], lw=2, label=f"ROC curve class {i} (area={roc_auc[i]:0.2f})")
    else:
        RocCurveDisplay.from_estimator(model.best_estimator_, X_test, y_test, ax=ax)

    ax.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], linestyle='--', color='Grey', lw=0.8)
    ax.grid(False)
    ax.set_title("ROC Curve", fontweight='bold')
    ax.set_xlim([0.0, 1.0])
    ax.set_ylim([0.0, 1.05])
    ax.set_xlabel("False Positive Rate")
    ax.set_ylabel("True Positive Rate")
    ax.legend(loc="lower right")

def plot_prec_recall_curve(model, X_test, y_test, ax, multiclass=False):

    f_scores = np.linspace(0.2, 0.8, num=4)
    for f_score in f_scores:
        x = np.linspace(0.01, 1)
        y = f_score * x / (2 * x - f_score)
        (l,) = plt.plot(x[y >= 0], y[y >= 0], color="gray", alpha=0.2)
        plt.annotate("f1={0:0.1f}".format(f_score), xy=(0.9, y[45] + 0.02))

    y_score = model.predict_proba(X_test)
    if multiclass:
        y_test_binarized = label_binarize(y_test, classes=[0, 1, 2, 3, 4])
        n_classes = y_test_binarized.shape[1]

        precision = dict()
        recall = dict()
        for i in range(n_classes):
            precision[i], recall[i], _ = precision_recall_curve(y_test_binarized[:, i],y_score[:, i])
            # ax.plot(recall[i], precision[i], lw=2, label='class {}'.format(i))
            display = PrecisionRecallDisplay(
                recall=recall[i],
                precision=precision[i],
            )
            display.plot(ax=ax, name=f"P-R class {i}")

        ax.legend(loc="best")
    else:
        precision, recall, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_test, y_score[:, 1])
        # ax.plot(recall, precision, lw=2, label='class {}')
        display = PrecisionRecallDisplay(
            recall=recall,
            precision=precision,
        )
        display.plot(ax=ax)

    ax.grid(False)
    ax.set_title("Precision-Recall Curve", fontweight='bold')
    ax.set_xlim([0.0, 1.0])
    ax.set_ylim([0.0, 1.05])
    ax.set_xlabel("Recall")
    ax.set_ylabel("Precision")

# Reverse one hot encoding
failure_types = []

for index, row in df.iterrows():
    if row['TWF'] == 0 and row['HDF'] == 0 and row['PWF'] == 0 and row['OSF'] == 0 and row['RNF'] == 0:
        failure_types.append('No failure')
    elif row['TWF'] == 1:
        failure_types.append('TWF')
    elif row['HDF'] == 1:
        failure_types.append('HDF')
    elif row['PWF'] == 1:
        failure_types.append('PWF')
    elif row['OSF'] == 1:
        failure_types.append('OSF')
    elif row['RNF'] == 1:
        failure_types.append('RNF')
